wrestlers-due-to-weight-restrictions-on-plane%2Famp_articleshow%2F104475146.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Of%20Nehru%2C%20Atheism%20And%20Spirituality%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMasti%20Venkatesh%20Iyengar%20(1891-1986)%2C%20the%20Kannada%20writer%2C%20shared%20a%20variety%20of%20sentiments%20towards%20Nehru.%20He%20admired%20his%20ideals%20of%20non-alignment%20and%20world%20peace.%20He%20was%20angry%20at%20his%20disapproval%20of%20the%20idea%20of%20linguistic%20states.%20He%20was%20simply%20exasperated%20at%20his%20secularism.%20In%201953%2C%20Masti's%20editorial%20in%20Jeevana%2C%20a%20monthly%20magazine%20he%20ran%2C%20recalled%20a%20newspaper%20reporting%20that%20Nehru%20would%20offer%20puja%20for%20Goddess%20Tulaja%20Bhavani%20in%20Maharashtra.%20The%20following%20day%2C%20that%20newspaper%20had%20clarified%20that%20he%20wouldn't%20offer%20puja%20there.%20While%20Nehru%20respected%20all%20forms%20of%20worship%2C%20the%20clarification%20continued%2C%20he%20never%20offered%20puja%20at%20any%20temple.%20Why%20was%20visiting%20a%20temple%2C%20Masti%20wondered%2C%20such%20a%20difficult%20idea%20for%20%26quot%3Bthe%20dharma%20of%20our%20modern%20people%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20editorial%20from%20the%20following%20year%2C%20Masti%20argued%20that%20Nehru's%20remark%20made%20at%20the%20inaugural%20occasion%20of%20the%20Bhakra%20Nangal%20Dam%20that%20such%20an%20achievement%20ought%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bworshipped%26quot%3B%20shared%20the%20same%20attitude%20that%20long%20held%20that%20the%20rivers%20Ganga%2C%20Yamuna%2C%20Cauvery%2C%20and%20Godavari%20be%20worshipped.%20A%20previous%20editorial%20of%20his%20had%20even%20claimed%20that%20the%20tolerance%20and%20generosity%20of%20Nehru%20were%20inherited%20from%20Hindu%20dharma.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWritten%20soon%20after%20Nehru's%20death%20in%201964%2C%20Masti's%20essay%20of%20condolence%20provided%20a%20lengthy%20survey%20of%20the%20leader's%20life%2C%20virtues%2C%20and%20achievements.%20The%20closing%20part%20of%20this%20essay%20shows%20him%2C%20yet%20again%2C%20refusing%20to%20read%20Nehru's%20secularism%20literally%3A%20%26quot%3BJawaharlal%20had%20thought%20that%20he%20was%20indifferent%20to%20matters%20of%20religion%20(dharma).%20Does%20the%20self%20(atman)%20exist%3F%20Is%20it%20eternal%3F%20Do%20god%20and%20heaven%20exist%3F%20These%20questions%20appeared%20unnatural%20to%20him.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BBut%2C%26quot%3B%20Masti%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3BNehru's%20actions%20were%20truly%20rooted%20in%20religion.%20The%20essence%20of%20religion%20is%20that%20one%20must%20secure%20the%20well-being%20of%20the%20world%2C%20without%20prioritizing%20one's%2C%20or%20one's%20family's%2C%20interests.%20Religions%20might%20preach%20this%20in%20the%20name%20of%20god%20while%20the%20modern%20mind%20might%20do%20so%20in%20the%20name%20of%20mankind.%20Although%20the%20act%20of%20achieving%20the%20goal%20might%20seem%20to%20differ%20a%20bit%2C%20the%20achievement%20is%20the%20same.%20A%20poet's%20spirit%20was%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20it%20all.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20why%2C%26quot%3B%20Masti%20observed%20further%2C%20%26quot%3BNehru%20overflowed%20with%20bhakti%20when%20he%20encountered%20persons%20with%20a%20noble%20consciousness%20such%20as%20Gandhi%20and%20Tagore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20speech%20delivered%20at%20a%20college%20in%20Madikeri%20in%201956%2C%20Kuvempu%20(1904-1994)%20tried%20to%20shake%20the%20student%20enthusiasm%20for%20Nehru's%20ideas%20of%20a%20modern%20India%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20looks%20like%20we%20are%20determined%20to%20live%20in%20a%20Masti%20Venkatesh%20Iyengar%20(1891-1986)%2C%20the%20Kannada%20writer%2C%20shared%20a%20variety%20of%20sentiments%20towards%20Nehru.%20He%20admired%20his%20ideals%20of%20non-alignment%20and%20world%20peace.%20He%20was%20angry%20at%20his%20disapproval%20of%20the%20idea%20of%20linguistic%20states.%20He%20was%20simply%20exasperated%20at%20his%20secularism.%20In%201953%2C%20Masti's%20editorial%20in%20Jeevana%2C%20a%20monthly%20magazine%20he%20ran%2C%20recalled%20a%20newspaper%20reporting%20that%20Nehru%20would%20offer%20puja%20for%20Goddess%20Tulaja%20Bhavani%20in%20Maharashtra.%20The%20following%20day%2C%20that%20newspaper%20had%20clarified%20that%20he%20wouldn't%20offer%20puja%20there.%20While%20Nehru%20respected%20all%20forms%20of%20worship%2C%20the%20clarification%20continued%2C%20that%20he%20never%20offered%20puja%20at%20any%20temple.%20Why%20was%20visiting%20a%20temple%2C%20Masti%20wondered%2C%20such%20a%20difficult%20idea%20for%20%26quot%3Bthe%20dharma%20of%20our%20modern%20people%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20editorial%20from%20the%20following%20year%2C%20Masti%20argued%20that%20Nehru's%20remark%20made%20at%20the%20inaugural%20occasion%20of%20the%20Bhakra%20Nangal%20Dam%20that%20such%20an%20achievement%20ought%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bworshipped%26quot%3B%20shared%20the%20same%20attitude%20that%20long%20held%20that%20the%20rivers%20Ganga%2C%20Yamuna%2C%20Cauvery%2C%20and%20Godavari%20be%20worshipped.%20A%20previous%20editorial%20of%20his%20had%20even%20claimed%20that%20the%20tolerance%20and%20generosity%20of%20Nehru%20were%20inherited%20from%20Hindu%20dharma.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWritten%20soon%20after%20Nehru's%20death%20in%201964%2C%20Masti's%20essay%20of%20condolence%20provided%20a%20lengthy%20survey%20of%20the%20leader's%20life%2C%20virtues%2C%20and%20achievements.%20The%20closing%20part%20of%20this%20essay%20shows%20him%2C%20yet%20again%2C%20refusing%20to%20read%20Nehru's%20secularism%20literally%3A%20%26quot%3BJawaharlal%20had%20thought%20that%20he%20was%20indifferent%20to%20matters%20of%20religion%20(dharma).%20Does%20the%20self%20(atman)%20exist%3F%20Is%20it%20eternal%3F%20Do%20god%20and%20heaven%20exist%3F%20These%20questions%20appeared%20unnatural%20to%20him.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BBut%2C%26quot%3B%20Masti%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3BNehru's%20actions%20were%20truly%20rooted%20in%20religion.%20The%20essence%20of%20religion%20is%20that%20one%20must%20secure%20the%20well-being%20of%20the%20world%2C%20without%20prioritizing%20one's%2C%20or%20one's%20family's%2C%20interests.%20Religions%20might%20preach%20this%20in%20the%20name%20of%20god%20while%20the%20modern%20mind%20might%20do%20so%20in%20the%20name%20of%20mankind.%20Although%20the%20act%20of%20achieving%20the%20goal%20might%20seem%20to%20differ%20a%20bit%2C%20the%20achievement%20is%20the%20same.%20A%20poet's%20spirit%20was%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20it%20all.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20why%2C%26quot%3B%20Masti%20observed%20further%2C%20%26quot%3BNehru%20overflowed%20with%20bhakti%20when%20he%20encountered%20persons%20with%20a%20noble%20consciousness%20such%20as%20Gandhi%20and%20Tagore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20speech%20delivered%20at%20a%20college%20in%20Madikeri%20in%201956%2C%20Kuvempu%20(1904-1994)%20tried%20to%20shake%20the%20student%20enthusiasm%20for%20Nehru's%20ideas%20of%20a%20modern%20India%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20looks%20like%20we%20are%20determined%20to%20live%20in%20a%20this-worldly%20(loukika)%20state%20and%20build%20factories%2C%20dams%2C%20and%20harness%20electricity.%20But%20what%20use%20are%20these%20if%20our%20consciousness%20is%20not%20shaped%20properly%20if%20it%20lacks%20light%2C%20radiance%2C%20guidance%2C%20and%20courage.%26quot%3B%20This%20Kannada%20writer's%20confident%20skepticism%20towards%20Nehru's%20modern%20ideals%20came%20from%20his%20own%20philosophical%20convictions%20which%20owed%20to%20advaita%20vedanta.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKuvempu's%20essay%20on%20Nehru's%20scientific%20vision%20and%20rationality%2C%20written%20a%20few%20months%20after%20the%20leader's%20death%20in%201964%2C%20offered%20an%20intriguing%20view.%20Dismissing%20any%20characterisation%20of%20Nehru%20as%20an%20atheist%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20that%20an%20acknowledgment%20of%20a%20force%20larger%20than%20himself%20could%20be%20seen%20in%20Nehru's%20writings%2C%20speeches%2C%20and%20letters%20and%20in%20his%20conduct%20and%20relations%20with%20elders.%20Anyone%20who%20saw%20the%20photos%20of%20Nehru%20and%20Vinoba%20Bhave%20at%20the%20Sarvodaya%20meeting%20in%20Mysore%20in%20the%20newspapers%20could%20not%20possibly%20mistake%20the%20former%20for%20an%20atheist.%20Nehru's%20body%20posture%20and%20facial%20gestures%20expressed%20sentiments%20that%20were%20impossible%20to%20describe%20fully.%20Older%20than%20Vinoba%2C%20and%20only%20second%20to%20Gandhi%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle%2C%20and%20an%20internationally%20renowned%20statesman%2C%20and%20immensely%20read%2C%20Nehru%20had%20still%20bowed%20to%20Vinoba.%20%C2%A0Authority%2C%20power%2C%20and%20honour%20had%20surrendered%20here%20to%20kindness%2C%20humility%2C%20charity%2C%20and%20devotion.%20This%20proved%20beyond%20doubt%2C%20for%20Kuvempu%2C%20that%20it%20was%20wrong%20to%20view%20Nehru%20as%20an%20atheist.%20In%20matters%20of%20sacrifice%2C%20love%20for%20the%20country%2C%20courage%2C%20empathy%2C%20intelligence%2C%20oratory%2C%20and%20writing%20talent%2C%20Kuvempu%20felt%20Nehru%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Bextraordinary%20man%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Bsome%20great%20spirituality%20was%20behind%20each%20one%20of%20these%20qualities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENehru%20might%20have%20openly%20sported%20his%20secular%20ideals%20and%20atheist%20outlook%20but%20Masti%20and%20Kuvempu%2C%20in%20their%20own%20distinct%20ways%2C%20hadn't%20taken%20it%20at%20face%20value.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20with%20permission%20from%20Another%20India%3A%20Events%2C%20Memories%2C%20People%20by%20Chandan%20Gowda%20(Simon%20and%20Schuster%20India%2C%202023.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDisclaimer%3A%20The%20author%20and%20publisher%20of%20the%20book%20are%20solely%20responsible%20for%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20book%20or%20any%20excerpt%20derived%20therefrom.%20NDTV%20shall%20not%20be%20responsible%20or%20liable%20for%20any%20claims%20arising%20from%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20book%20in