flict%20began%2C%20with%20at%20least%201%2C300%20casualties%20reported.%20Scholz's%20visit%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20significant%20step%2C%20as%20he%20will%20be%20the%20first%20prime%20minister%20to%20visit%20Israel%20since%20the%20conflict%20erupted.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fgermanys-scholz-to-visit-israel-and-egypt-this-week%2Farticleshow%2F104474955.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fgermanys-scholz-to-visit-israel-and-egypt-this-week%2Famp_articleshow%2F104474955.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fgermanys-scholz-to-visit-israel-and-egypt-this-week%2Famp_articleshow%2F104474955.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BBetrayal%20Of%20Public%20Trust%26quot%3B%3A%20Court%20Slams%20Investigators%20In%20Nithari%20Judgment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20handling%20of%20the%20Nithari%20case%2C%20which%20involved%20serial%20killings%20of%20children%20in%20Delhi's%20backyard%20Noida%2C%20was%20%26quot%3Bbotched%26quot%3B%20and%20was%20%26quot%3Bnothing%20short%20of%20betrayal%20of%20public%20trust%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20has%20said%20in%20a%20scathing%20criticism%20of%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20and%20the%20Noida%20Police.%20The%20presentation%20of%20the%20case%20in%20court%20also%20left%20much%20to%20be%20desired%2C%20the%20judges%20indicated%2C%20saying%20the%20prosecution%20has%20failed%20to%20prove%20guilt%20beyond%20reasonable%20doubt%20and%20left%20key%20angles%2C%20including%20the%20possibility%20of%20an%20organized%20organ%20trade%2C%20unexplored.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20horrific%20case%20that%20shocked%20the%20nation%2017%20years%20ago%2C%20brought%20to%20light%20the%20murder%20and%20dismemberment%20of%2019%20children%20and%20at%20least%20one%20woman.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%20today%2C%20the%20court%20cleared%20main%20accused%20Surinder%20Koli%20of%20all%20charges%20in%2012%20cases.%20His%20employer%20and%20co-accused%20Moninder%20Singh%20Pandher%20was%20acquitted%20in%20two%20cases.%20Their%20death%20sentences%20have%20been%20cancelled.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20investigation%20otherwise%20is%20botched%20up%20and%20basic%20norms%20of%20collecting%20evidence%20have%20been%20brazenly%20violated%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said%20in%20its%20detailed%20order.%C2%A0%20The%20manner%20of%20arrest%2C%20recovery%20of%20evidence%20and%20recording%20of%20confession%20was%20%26quot%3Bcasual%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bperfunctory%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20appears%20to%20us%20that%20the%20investigation%20opted%20for%20the%20easy%20course%20of%20implicating%20a%20poor%20servant%20of%20the%20house%20by%20demonizing%20him%2C%20without%20taking%20due%20care%20of%20probing%20more%20serious%20aspects%20of%20possible%20involvement%20of%20organized%20activity%20of%20organ%20trading%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20the%20order%20in%20the%20case%20that%20was%20based%20on%20confession%20of%20Pander's%20domestic%20help%20Surinder%20Koli.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20investigators%20said%20Koli%20had%20confessed%20to%20the%20murder%2C%20rape%20of%20dead%20bodies%20and%20consumption%20of%20human%20flesh.%20The%20murders%20took%20place%20in%20Pandher's%20house%20in%20Noida%2C%20and%20the%20men%20were%20arrested%20in%20December%202006%20after%20body%20parts%20were%20found%20in%20an%20adjacent%20drain.%20In%20the%20months%20before%20that%20a%20number%20of%20children%20were%20reported%20to%20be%20missing%20from%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stand%20of%20the%20prosecution%20kept%20changing%20from%20time%20to%20time%E2%80%A6%20Failure%20of%20investigation%20to%20probe%20involvement%20of%20organ%20trade%2C%20despite%20specific%20recommendations%20made%20by%20High%20level%20committee%20constituted%20by%20the%20ministry%20of%20women%20%26amp%3B%20child%20development%20in%20Nithari%20Killings%20is%20nothing%20short%20of%20a%20betrayal%20of%20public%20trust%20by%20responsible%20agencies%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judgment%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20manner%20in%20which%20confession%20is%20recorded%20after%2060%20days%20of%20police%20remand%20without%20any%20medical%20examination%20of%20accused%3B%20providing%20of%20legal%20aid%3B%20overlooking%20specific%20allegation%20of%20torture%20in%20the%20confession%20itself%3B%20failure%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20requirement%20of%20Section%20164%20CrPC%20is%20shocking%20to%20say%20the%20least%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKoli%20was%20awarded%20five%20death%20sentences%20in%20five%20separate%20cases%2C%20but%20had%20a%20narrow%20shave%20twice.%20In%202014%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20upheld%20the%20death%20penalty%20after%20putting%20the%20execution%20on%20hold%20for%20a%20month.%20The%20matter%20had%20also%20reached%20then%20President%20Pranab%20Mukherjee.%20Mr%20Mukherjee%20rejected%20Koli's%20mercy%20petition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20next%20year%2C%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20commuted%20the%20death%20penalty%20to%20life%20imprisonment%2C%20citing%20the%20%26quot%3Binordinate%26quot%3B%20delay%20in%20deciding%20his%20mercy%20plea.%20Pandher%20is%20currently%20in%20a%20Noida%20jail%2C%20and%20Koli%20is%20in%20a%20jail%20in%20Ghaziabad.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697469060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fmdg1rqb8_nithari_625x300_16_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbetrayal-of-public-trust-court-slams-investigators-in-nithari-judgment-4486508%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20prosecution%20has%20failed%20to%20prove%20guilt%20in%20the%20Nithari%20case%20beyond%20a%20reasonable%20doubt%20and%20left%20key%20angles%2C%20including%20the%20possibility%20of%20an%20organized%20organ%20trade%2C%20unexplored%2C%20the%20Allah