ew%20recorded%20on%20Monday%2C%20October%2016%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20former%20deputy%20foreign%20minister%20Danny%20Ayalon%20%E2%80%93%20who%20also%20served%20as%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20to%20Washington%20%E2%80%93%20responds%20to%20all%20the%20tough%20questions%20about%20his%20country%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20the%20Hamas%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FqTDjC955CJ0%3Fsi%3DKPPQdw5jr3AODoG0%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20the%20list%20of%20the%20questions%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E1)%20I%20want%20to%20start%20with%20a%20few%20questions%20that%20are%20being%20asked%20in%20India%20and%20get%20your%20response%20to%20them.%20There%E2%80%99s%20no%20doubt%20what%20Hamas%20has%20done%20is%20horrendous%2C%20deeply%20condemnable%20and%20completely%20unforgivable.%20But%20in%20response%20by%20cutting%20off%20electricity%2C%20fuel%20and%20food%20and%20only%20restoring%20water%20to%20southern%20Gaza%20yesterday%20evening%20%E2%80%93%20and%20not%20even%20permitting%20Egypt%20to%20send%20in%20supplies%20%E2%80%93%20Israel%20is%20inflicting%20collective%20punishment%20on%20all%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza%20when%20the%20vast%20majority%20are%20innocent%20civilians.%20How%20is%20this%20justified%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E2)%20You%E2%80%99ve%20also%20ordered%201.1%20million%20people%20in%20Gaza%20north%20of%20Wadi%20Gaza%20to%20move%20south%20and%20initially%20gave%20them%2024%20hours%20to%20do%20so%20which%20has%20now%20stretched%20to%2036%20or%2048%20hours.%20Not%20only%20is%20that%20close%20to%20impossible%20to%20comply%20with%20when%20there%20is%20no%20fuel%20and%20people%20have%20to%20walk%20but%20what%20about%20the%20elderly%20and%20those%20in%20hospitals%20who%20can%E2%80%99t%20leave%3F%20And%20where%20do%20they%20stay%20in%20the%20south%3F%20You%E2%80%99re%20effectively%20making%20them%20refugees%20in%20their%20own%20country%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E3)%20The%20Israeli%20army%20has%20announced%20it%20will%20attack%20Gaza%20by%20land%2C%20sea%20and%20air%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20believed%20that%20could%20happen%20quite%20soon.%20How%20confident%20are%20you%20that%20you%20can%20obliterate%20Hamas%20and%20its%20infrastructure%20much%20of%20which%20is%20hidden%20in%20a%20labyrinth%20of%20tunnels%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E4)%20Are%20you%20worried%20that%20the%20measures%20you%E2%80%99re%20taking%20may%20succeed%20in%20tackling%20the%20problem%20you%20face%20but%20they%20will%20also%20lead%20to%20enormous%20and%20long-lasting%20grievance%20and%20hurt%20amongst%20the%20Palestinian%20people%3F%20They%20see%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20as%20a%20second%20%3Cem%3ENakba%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20could%20motivate%20many%20to%20seek%20revenge%20and%20create%20a%20far%20bigger%20future%20problem%20for%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E5)%20It%20seems%20President%20Isaac%20Herzog%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20accept%20any%20distinction%20between%20civilians%20in%20Gaza%20and%20Hamas.%20He%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20an%20entire%20nation%20out%20there%20that%20is%20responsible.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20true%20this%20rhetoric%20about%20civilians%20not%20being%20aware%2C%20not%20involved.%20It%E2%80%99s%20absolutely%20not%20true.%20They%20could%20have%20risen%20up.%20They%20could%20have%20fought%20against%20that%20evil%20regime%20which%20took%20over%20Gaza%20in%20a%20coup%20d%E2%80%99%C3%A9tat.%E2%80%9D%20Does%20that%20suggest%20Israel%20is%20out%20to%20obliterate%20not%20just%20Hamas%20but%20the%20entire%20Palestine%20population%20of%20Gaza%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E6)%20Last%20week%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ll%20change%20the%20Middle%20East%20forever.%E2%80%9D%20Defence%20minister%20Yoav%20Gallant%20said%20Gaza%20will%20never%20go%20back%20to%20what%20it%20was.%20Was%20that%20just%20angry%20rhetoric%20in%20the%20heat%20of%20the%20moment%3F%20Because%20if%20they%20meant%20it%20and%20try%20to%20implement%20it%20won%E2%80%99t%20you%20provoke%20Hezbollah%20and%20Iran%20to%20enter%20the%20conflict%3F%20In%20fact%2C%20this%20could%20also%20have%20serious%20repercussions%20in%20Riyadh.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E7)%20Last%20week%20whilst%20addressing%20Jewish%20leaders%20in%20Washington%2C%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20said%20Israel%20must%20observe%20the%20rules%20of%20war.%20Separately%20US%20secretary%20of%20state%20Antony%20Blinken%2C%20whilst%20standing%20beside%20Prime%20Minister%20Netanyahu%2C%20said%20Israel%20must%20avoid%20killing%20innocent%20civilians.%20Do%20you%20accept%20these%20were%20gentle%20warnings%20not%20to%20do%20something%20your%20friends%20would%20find%20difficult%20to%20defend%20or%20even%20ignore%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E8)%20Let%E2%80%99s%20briefly%20widen%20our%20discussion.%20In%20the%20last%20few%20years%20before%20the%20Hamas%20attack%2C%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20were%20drawing%20Israel%20closer%20to%20many%20of%20the%20Arab%20and%20Muslim%20countries%20of%20the%20Middle%20East.%20You%20were%20even%20poised%20to%20sign%20a%20path-breaking%20deal%20with%20Saudi%20Arabia.%20Now%20Riyadh%20has%20said%20that%20the%20deal%20is%20on%20pause%20but%20has%20the%20wider%20rapprochement%20also%20been%20checked%20and%20stalled%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E9)%20As%20we%20speak%2C%20King%20Abdullah%20of%20Jordan%20is%20in%20Europe%20to%20try%20to%20stop%20a%20war%20in%20Gaza.%20Secretary%20Blinken%20has%20visited%20many%20Arab%20capitals%20over%20the%20last%20few%20days.%20Even%20the%20Russian%20deputy%20foreign%20minister%20says%20he%20will%20meet%20with%20Hamas%20officials%20in%20Qatar%20this%20week.%20From%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%2C%20if%20this%20diplomacy%20can%20produce%20an%20agreement%20to%20exchange%20Israeli%20hostages%20for%20Palestinian%20prisoners%2C%20could%20that%20restrain%20your%20hand%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAre%20you%20prepared%20to%20attack%20Gaza%20even%20at%20at%20the%20risk%20of%20your%20hostages%20being%20killed%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E10)%20Finally%2C%20how%20do%20you%20view%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20stand%3F%20For%20the%20first%20few%20days%2C%20it%20was%20expressed%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20tweets%20expressing%20solidarity%20with%20Israel%20and%20stating%20India%20stands%20firmly%20behind%20Israel.%20He%20also%20called%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20terrorism.%20But%20on%20Friday%2C%20the%20foreign%20ministry%20modified%20that%20by%20adding%20India%20advocates%20the%20resumption%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdirect%20negotiations%E2%80%9D%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Csovereign%2C%20independent%20and%20viable%20state%20of%20Palestine%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20there%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20universal%20obligation%20to%20observe%20international%20humanitarian%20law%E2%80%9D.%20How%20do%20you%20view%20that%20change%20in%20the%20Indian%20position%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E11)%20My%20last%20question%3A%20Prime%20Minister%20Netanyahu%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20accept%20a%20two-nation%20solution.%20But%20how%20do%20you%20respond%20to%20the%20view%20that%20a%20two-nation%20solution%20%E2%80%93%20which%20probably%20would%20involve%20dismantling%20many%20Israeli%20settlements%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20accepting%20East%20Jerusalem%20as%20the%20Palestinian%20capital%20%E2%80%93%20is%20the%20most%20likely%20way%20of%20resolving%20this%20problem%20that%E2%80%99s%20lasted%20nearly%2075%20years%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E12)%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20future%3A%20Is%20the%20end%20in%20sight%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697455905000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16165926%2FKT-16-Oct-B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-karan-thapar-danny-ayalon-israel-hamas-interview%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Karan%20Thapar%20interviews%20Israel%