20Nations%2C%20Japan%2C%20Thailand%20and%20European%20Union.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20was%20another%20signing%20ceremony%20in%20February%202018%20for%20two%20other%20groups.%20To%20mark%20it%2C%20the%20MEA%20had%20issued%20a%20statement%20reiterating%20that%20India%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F29482%2FOfficial_Spokespersons_response_to_a_query_on_Indias_presence_at_the_signing_of_National_Ceasefire_Agreement_in_Myanmar%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esupports%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20Myanmar%20peace%20process%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESignifying%20the%20change%20in%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20international%20status%20since%20the%20coup%2C%20only%20three%20foreign%20countries%20who%20were%20international%20witnesses%20to%20the%20NCA%20took%20part%20in%20the%20commemorations%20this%20time%20%E2%80%93%20India%2C%20China%20and%20Thailand.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20delegation%20was%20led%20by%20deputy%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Vikram%20Misri%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20former%20Indian%20ambassador%20to%20the%20south-east%20Asian%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20was%20no%20statement%20or%20press%20note%20from%20the%20Indian%20side%2C%20but%20the%20Myanmar%20government%20highlighted%20the%20participation%20from%20the%20foreign%20countries%20through%20their%20information%20ministry%20and%20state%20media.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Misri%20told%20the%20gathering%20that%20the%20NCA%20could%20be%20the%20platform%20for%20political%20reforms%20to%20reflect%20the%20aspirations%20of%20Myanmar%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdemocratic%20and%20federal%20republic%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20inclusive%20society%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20speech%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.myanmarseo.com%2Ffile%2Fclient-cdn%2F2023%2F10%2F16_Oct_23_gnlm.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epublished%20in%20the%20state%20newspaper%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGlobal%20New%20Light%20for%20Myanmar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Misri%20said%20that%20the%20NCA%20had%20visualised%20a%20country%20where%20the%20%E2%80%9Crich%20tapestry%20of%20ethnic%20voices%20and%20cultures%20is%20not%20just%20respected%20but%20celebrated%2C%20where%20every%20individual%20has%20the%20opportunity%20to%20flourish%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStating%20this%20spirit%20needed%20to%20be%20further%20strengthened%2C%20Misri%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndia%2C%20as%20a%20federal%20democratic%20country%2C%20supports%20this%20path%20for%20Myanmar%20and%20has%20always%20lent%20a%20helping%20hand%20whenever%20needed%20through%20its%20initiatives%20like%20promoting%20dialogue%20on%20constitutionalism%20and%20federalism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20not%20referring%20to%20coup%20directly%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20have%20been%20setbacks%20along%20the%20way%2C%20and%20the%20path%20forward%20remains%20challenging%20in%20view%20of%20the%20evolving%20political%20landscape%20in%20Myanmar%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENoting%20that%20Myanmar%20was%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmidst%20of%20a%20political%20transition%E2%80%9D%2C%20Misri%20said%20that%20the%20NCA%20framework%20could%20%E2%80%9Cprovide%20a%20platform%20for%20political%20reforms%20that%20reflect%20the%20aspirations%20of%20the%20Myanmar%20people%20for%20a%20democratic%20and%20federal%20republic%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20call%20upon%20all%20stakeholders%20to%20strengthen%20this%20framework%2C%20abide%20by%20their%20commitments%20and%20initiate%20a%20serious%20dialogue%20to%20resolve%20the%20conflict%20politically%20to%20move%20towards%20the%20goal%20of%20a%20federal%20democratic%20republic%20where%20all%20its%20people%20live%20in%20peace%2C%20stability%20and%20prosperity%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Chinese%20representative%20said%20that%20the%20Myanmar%20peace%20process%2C%20based%20on%20%E2%80%9Copenness%2C%20inclusivity%2C%20flexibility%20and%20practicality%2C%E2%80%9D%20will%20hold%20dialogues%20to%20achieve%20peace%20%E2%80%9Cthrough%20building%20mutual%20trust%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%20Special%20Envoy%20for%20Asian%20Affairs%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%20Deng%20Xijun%20called%20for%20accelerating%20Chinese%20projects%20in%20Myanmar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpeaking%20at%20the%20same%20forum%2C%20Thai%20vice-minister%20for%20Foreign%20Affairs%2C%20Sihasak%20Phuangketkeow%20urged%20%E2%80%9Call%20parties%20in%20Myanmar%20to%20stay%20the%20course%E2%80%9D%20of%20dialogue%20and%20engagement.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20urge%20all%20parties%20to%20persevere%20and%20overcome%20the%20challenges%20that%20lie%20ahead%2C%20in%20order%20to%20find%20a%20way%20forward%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Myanmar%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThree%20of%20the%20original%20NCA%20ethnic%20armed%20groups%20signatories%20Karen%20National%20Union%2C%20Chin%20National%20Front%20and%20All%20Burma%20Students%E2%80%99%20Democratic%20Front%20boycotted%20Sunday%E2%80%99s%20ceremony.%20They%20have%20allied%20themselves%20with%20two%20other%20armed%20groups%2C%20Kachin%20Independence%20Army%20(KIA)%20and%20the%20Karenni%20National%20Progressive%20Party%20(KNPP)%2C%20who%20have%20been%20fighting%20against%20the%20Junta.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECrucially%2C%20many%20of%20the%20pro-democracy%20forces%20have%20also%20joined%20hands%20with%20these%20ethnic%20groups%20and%20the%20Junta%20has%20been%20facing%20an%20armed%20resistance%20in%20major%20swathes%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20April%202022%2C%20the%20junta%20leadership%20has%20been%20meeting%20with%20members%20of%20various%20ethnic%20armed%20groups%2C%20including%20the%20remaining%20seven%20NCA%20signatories.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20commentators%2C%20the%20Tatmadaw%E2%80%99s%20outreach%20could%20be%20a%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmizzima.com%2Farticle%2Fmyanmar-junta-seeks-divide-and-rule-eao-peace-talks%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edivide%20and%20rule%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20ploy%20and%20to%20stop%20them%20from%20aligning%20with%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20National%20Unity%20Government%20(NUG).%20There%20were%20also%20reports%20that%20Junta%20was%20talking%20with%20the%20armed%20groups%20to%20hold%20elections%20in%20their%20territory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20military%E2%80%99s%20promises%20of%20general%20elections%2C%20pro-democracy%20activists%20remain%20sceptical%2C%20expressing%20concerns%20that%20such%20elections%2C%20even%20if%20conducted%2C%20would%20not%20be%20conducted%20in%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20manner.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20presence%20at%20the%20Junta%E2%80%99s%20NCA%20commemorative%20event%20is%20not%20surprising%20as%20New%20Delhi%20has%20remained%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2022%2F11%2Findia-engages-myanmar%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eengaged%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20Nyay%20Pyi%20Taw%20with%20regular%20high-level%20visits%20from%20Indian%20officials%20even%20after%20the%20February%202021%20coup.%20This%20was%20a%20manifestation%20of%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20apprehension%20regarding%20the%20Tatmadaw%E2%80%99s%20growing%20ties%20with%20China%2C%20driven%20by%20their%20diplomatic%20isolation%2C%20and%20their%20need%20for%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Junta%20to%20ensure%20security%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20north-eastern%20region.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20day%20earlier%20on%20Saturday%2C%20October%2014%2C%20Vikram%20Misri%20had%20also%20called%20on%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20top%20military%20leader%20Senior%20General%20Min%20Aung%20Hlaing%2C%20who%20brought%20up%20%E2%80%9Ccooperation%20with%20India%20in%20peace%20and%20stability%20measures%20in%20border%20regions%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20per%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmyanmar.gov.mm%2Fnews-media%2Fnews%2F-%2Fasset_publisher%2F9ZewUq5mfR5F%2Fcontent%2F%2525E1%252580%252594%2525E1%252580%2525AD%2525E1%252580%2525AF%2525E1%252580%252584%2525E1%252580%2525BA%2525E1%252580%252584%2525E1%252580%2525B6%2525E1%252580%252590%2525E1%252580%2525B1%2525E1%252580%2525AC%2525E1%252580%2525BA%2525E1%252580%252585%2525E1%252580%2525AE%2525E1%252580%252599%2525E1%252580%2525B6%2525E1%252580%2525A1%2525-1286%3F_com_liferay_asset_publisher_web_portlet_AssetPublisherPortlet_INSTANCE_9ZewUq5mfR5F_redirect%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fmyanmar.gov.mm%252Fnews-media%252Fnews%253Fp_p_id%253Dcom_liferay_asset_publisher_web_portlet_AssetPublisherPortlet_INSTANCE_9ZewUq5mfR5F%2526p_p_lifecycle%253D0%2526p_p_state%253Dnormal%2526p_p_mode%253Dview%2526_com_liferay_asset_publisher_web_portlet_AssetPublisherPortlet_INSTANCE_9ZewUq5mfR5F_cur%253D8%2526_com_liferay_asset_publisher_web_portlet_AssetPublisherPortlet_INSTANCE_9ZewUq5mfR5F_delta%253D10%2526p_r_p_resetCur%253Dfalse%2526_com_liferay_asset_publisher_web_portlet_AssetPublisherPortlet_INSTANCE_9ZewUq5mfR5F_assetEntryId%253D205609481%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereadout%20from%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20information%20ministry%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20expressed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gnlm.com.mm%2Fmyanmars-ongoing-quest-for-internal-peace-receives-assistance-from-india%2F%3F__cf_chl_tk%3Dio0FV1QFJwsaWVHjFi7qI8ugrOFvOhkoiy7q4PtS5Cg-1697445602-0-gaNycGzNDtA%23article-title%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eappreciation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20India%20%E2%80%9Cassisting%E2%80%9D%20in%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20peace%20process%2C%20while%20the%20government%20was%20striving%20to%20%E2%80%9Crestore%20internal%20peace%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697449850000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16150629%2FUntitled-design-12.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Findia-myanmar-ceasefire-anniversary-junta%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20is%20the%20first%20time%20that%20the%20Myanmar%20junta%20has%20hosted%20a%20public%20event%20with%20ethnic%20leaders%20since%20the%20military%20coup%20toppled%20the%20civilian%20government%20and%20imprisoned%20civilian%20leaders%2C%20including%20Aung%20San%20Suu%20Kyi.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Findia-myanmar-ceasefire-anniversary-junta%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Unpaid%20Labour%20on%20the%20Rise%2C%20Muslims%20Not%20Looking%20For%20Work%3A%20What%20the%20PLFS%20Data%20Reveals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16134843%2Fimage-1392.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20significant%20number%20of%20individuals%20in%20India%20are%20engaging%20in%20self-employment%20or%20unpaid%20labour%2C%20shows%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mospi.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpublication_reports%2FAR_PLFS_2022_23N.pdf%3Fdownload%3D1%5C%22%3EPeriodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%20(PLFS)%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20July%202022%20to%20June%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20data%20highlights%20that%2C%20among%20the%20major%20religious%20groups%2C%20only%20Muslims%20have%20experienced%20a%20decline%20in%20their%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20(LFPR)%20and%20worker%20population%20ratio%20(WPR).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20PLFS%20was%20launched%20by%20the%20National%20Sample%20Survey%20Office%20in%20April%202017.%20It%20e%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estimates%20the%20key%20employment%20and%20unemployment%20indicators%20such%20as%20Worker%20Population%20Ratio%2C%20Labour%20Force%20Participation%20Rate%2C%20and%20Unemployment%20Rate.%20It%20further%20measures%20the%20employment%20status%20among%20social%20and%20religious%20groups.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20major%20religious%20groups%2C%20it%20names%20%E2%80%9CHinduism%2C%20Islam%2C%20Christianity%20and%20Sikhism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20positive%20note%2C%20the%20latest%20data%20indicates%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20unemployment%20rate%20for%20individuals%20aged%2015%20and%20above%20has%20reached%20a%20six-year%20low%2C%20standing%20at%203.2%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20shows%20a%20decrease%20in%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20in%20rural%20areas%20from%205.3%25%20in%202017-18%20to%202.4%25%20in%202022-23%2C%20and%20in%20urban%20areas%20from%207.7%25%20to%205.4%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20statistics%20may%20seem%20encouraging%20at%20first%20glance%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20essential%20to%20examine%20the%20finer%20details%20to%20gain%20a%20more%20comprehensive%20understanding%20of%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20increasing%20share%20in%20self-employment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20PLFS%20data%2C%20a%20larger%20number%20of%20individuals%20are%20self-employed%20than%20those%20in%20casual%20labour%20and%20the%20regular%20salaried%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20urban%20areas%2C%20a%20relatively%20higher%20number%20of%20people%20have%20salaried%20jobs%20as%20opposed%20to%20self-employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20PLFS%20divides%20employment%20status%20for%20workers%20into%20three%20broad%20categories%3A%20(i)%20self-employed%2C%20(ii)%20regular%20wage%20or%20salaried%20employees%2C%20and%20(iii)%20casual%20labour.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20overall%20rate%20of%20self-employed%20people%20increased%20to%2057.3%25%20in%202022-23%20from%2055.8%25%20in%202021-22%20and%2055.6%25%20in%202020-21.%20It%20was%20around%2052%25%20in%202017-18%20and%202018-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENote%20that%202022-23%20refers%20to%20the%20period%20from%20July%202022%20to%20June%202023%20and%20likewise%20for%202021-22%2C%202020-21%2C%202019-20%2C%202018-19%20and%202017-18.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F11142702%2Fimage-1378.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221015%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F11142702%2Fimage-1378.png%201015w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F11142702%2Fimage-1378-300x163.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-679477%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22552%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F11142652%2Fimage-1379.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221011%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F11142652%2Fimage-1379.png%201011w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F11142652%2Fimage-1379-300x183.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-679476%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22618%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20self-employed%20category%2C%20two%20sub-categories%20have%20been%20established%2C%20which%20include%3A%20(i)%20own%20account%20workers%20and%20employers%2C%20and%20(ii)%20unpaid%20helpers%20in%20household%20enterprises.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20%5Bthe%5D%20employer%20%5Bcategory%5D%20is%20barely%20under%202%25%20of%20the%20number%20of%20people%20in%20the%20economy.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20own%20account%20workers%E2%80%99%20category%20is%20highly%20driven%20by%20people%20such%20as%20the%20cultivators%2C%20weavers%2C%20potters%2C%20who%20work%20on%20their%20own%2C%20in%20rural%20areas.%20And%20in%20urban%20areas%2C%20they%20are%20the%20%3Cem%3Eredi%3C%2Fem%3E%20walas%2C%20%3Cem%3Ethele%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewalas%2C%20kabaadi%2C%20barbers%2C%20tailors%2C%20vendors%2C%20those%20who%E2%80%99re%20working%20on%20the%20street.%20The%20share%20of%20self-employed%20%5Bpeople%5D%20in%20the%20total%20workforce%20is%20increasing%2C%20and%20within%20that%20most%20of%20the%20increase%20can%20be%20seen%20among%20unpaid%20family%20labour%20and%20own%20account%20workers%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Santosh%20Mehrotra%2C%20professor%20of%20economics%2C%20Centre%20for%20Informal%20Sector%20and%20Labour%20Studies%2C%20School%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnpaid%20labour%C2%A0%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20categorised%20as%20%E2%80%98helper%20in%20household%20enterprise%E2%80%99%20within%20self-employment%20%E2%80%93%20has%20increased%20to%2018.3%25%20in%202022-23%20from%2017.5%25%20in%202021-22%20and%2017.3%25%20in%202020-21.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20regular%20worker%20gets%20a%20salary%2C%20an%20unpaid%20family%20labour%20within%20the%20self-employed%20gets%20nothing%3B%20an%20own%20account%20worker%2C%20%5Bas%20earlier%20mentioned%5D%2C%20is%20someone%20who%20in%20rural%20areas%20is%20a%20cultivator%20and%20will%20earn%20something%20when%20their%20crop%20is%20finished%20and%20%5Bwhen%5D%20they%20sell%20it.%20So%2C%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20is%20that%20regular%20people%20%5Bwho%20have%5D%20lost%20work%20have%20gone%20to%20do%20something%20on%20their%20own%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20explained%20that%20people%20are%20choosing%20to%20be%20self-employed%2C%20because%20of%20a%20lack%20of%20good%20work%20and%20wages.%20For%20example%2C%20an%20educated%20person%20would%20not%20want%20to%20do%20casual%20labour%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20elaborated%20saying%3A%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20casual%20labour%20has%20reverse%20migrated%20back%20to%20his%20village%2C%20then%20he%20could%20be%20now%20doing%20MGNREGA%20(National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Programme)%20work%20sometimes%2C%20or%20has%20gone%20back%20to%20work%20on%20his%20family%20farm.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20another%20situation%20where%20women%20who%20had%20dropped%20out%20of%20the%20workforce%20return%20only%20to%20help%20their%20husbands.%20And%20that%20has%20happened%20consistently%2C%20on%20a%20massive%20scale%2C%20and%20distress%20has%20increased%20in%20the%20economy%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fthe-stories-of-women-who-migrate-alongside-their-husbands-to-work-as-helpers%5C%22%3EThe%20Stories%20of%20Women%20Who%20Migrate%20Alongside%20Their%20Husbands%20to%20Work%20as%20%E2%80%98Helpers%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20wish%20to%20call%20this%20kind%20of%20distress-driven%20employment%20%E2%80%99employment%E2%80%99%2C%20%5Bmay%5D%20god%20help%20you.%20This%20is%20the%20main%20reason%20why%20unemployment%20rate%20is%20supposedly%20decreasing%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Fexplainspeaking-gdp-growth-employment-india-8956297%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20its%20editorial%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20published%20in%20September%202023%2C%20underscored%20the%20need%20to%20appreciate%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20jobs%20being%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20instance%2C%20providing%20%E2%80%9Ccasual%20labour%E2%80%9D%20at%20a%20MGNREGA%20worksite%20or%20a%20construction%20worksite%20or%20working%20part-time%20in%20one%E2%80%99s%20family%20enterprise%20without%20any%20pay%20(%E2%80%9Cself-employment%E2%80%9D)%20are%20very%20poor%20substitutes%20for%20holding%20a%20job%20that%20provides%20a%20regular%20wage%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehrotra%20further%20asked%20why%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findias-workforce-not-rising-quality-of-jobs-very-low-cmies-mahesh-vyas%5C%22%3ECMIE%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20showing%20the%20opposite.%20This%20is%20because%E2%80%9D%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20include%20unpaid%20family%20labour%20as%20employment%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20CMIE%2C%20the%20Indian%20youth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Feditorials%2Fexpress-view-on-cmie-data-a-dissonant-note-8904516%2F%5C%22%3Eis%20increasingly%20getting%20driven%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20job%20market%2C%20and%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20workforce%20is%20ageing%2C%20which%20should%20be%20a%20matter%20of%20concern%20for%20policymakers.%20%E2%80%9CCMIE%20also%20shows%20that%20unemployment%20rate%20rose%2C%20and%20labour%20force%20and%20employment%20rates%20(as%20a%20share%20of%20the%20total%20in%20working%20age)%20both%20fell%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20employment%20numbers%20in%20other%20sectors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20that%2C%20the%20percentage%20of%20people%20in%20better%20paying%20jobs%20such%20as%20manufacturing%2C%20construction%2C%20etc.%20have%20remained%20stagnant%20but%2C%20as%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20the%20number%20of%20self-employed%20people%20has%20relatively%20increased.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20percentage%20of%20people%20working%20in%20the%20manufacturing%20sector%20was%2011.4%25%20in%202022-23.%20It%20was%20slightly%20higher%20at%2011.6%25%20in%202021-22%2C%20and%20in%20the%20preceding%20year%2C%20it%20stood%20at%2010.9%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20percentage%20of%20people%20working%20in%20the%20construction%20sector%20was%2013%25%20in%202022-23.%20It%20was%2012.4%25%20and%2012.1%25%20in%202021-22%20and%202020-21%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20people%20working%20in%20the%20trade%2C%20hotel%20and%20restaurant%20sector%20remained%20stagnant%20at%20around%2012%25%20from%202020%20to%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20trend%20can%20be%20observed%20in%20the%20percentage%20of%20people%20working%20in%20the%20transport%2C%20storage%2C%20and%20communications%20sectors%2C%20where%20only%20around%205%25%20were%20employed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20the%20percentage%20of%20regular%20wage%2Fsalaried%20employees%2C%20who%20are%20not%20eligible%20for%20any%20specified%20social%20security%20benefits%2C%20in%20rural%20India%2C%20has%20risen%20to%20around%2060%25%20in%202022-23%20from%2058.2%25%20and%2059.1%25%20in%202021-22%20and%202020-21%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20urban%20areas%2C%20the%20percentage%20has%20declined%20from%2050.1%25%20in%202020-21%20to%2049.4%25%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20overall%2C%20the%20percentage%20has%20remained%20stagnant%20at%20around%2054%25%20for%20all%20these%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Findia-narendra-modi-jobs-unemployment%5C%22%3EThree%20Claims%20of%20Government%20Economists%20About%20Jobs%20Put%20to%20the%20Test%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EData%20shows%20Muslims%20are%20not%20looking%20for%20work%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20PLFS%20survey%20shows%20that%20among%20major%20religious%20groups%2C%20the%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20(LFPR)%20and%20worker%20population%20ratio%20(WPR)%20of%20only%20Muslims%20have%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20is%20the%20share%20of%20population%20which%20is%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20and%20the%20worker%20population%20ratio%20is%20the%20share%20of%20the%20working%20age%20population%20that%20has%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20LFPR%20for%20ages%2015%20years%20and%20above%20increased%20to%2057.9%25%20in%202022-23%20from%2055.2%25%20in%202021-22%20and%2054.9%25%20in%202020-21.%20It%20was%2049.8%25%20in%202017-18%20and%2050.2%25%20in%202018-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20WPR%20for%20persons%20of%20ages%2015%20years%20and%20above%20increased%20to%2056%25%20in%202022-23%20from%2052.9%25%20in%202021-22%20and%2052.6%25%20in%202020-21.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20LFPR%20and%20WPR%20for%20only%20the%20Muslim%20community%20has%20fallen.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Muslims%2C%20the%20LFPR%20stood%20at%20around%2035.5%25%20in%202020-21%20and%2035.1%25%20in%202021-22.%20It%20declined%20to%2032.5%25%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20other%20words%2C%20from%20lower%20than%20national%20LFPR%20and%20WPR%2C%20Muslims%20have%20seen%20further%20falls%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mehrotra%20said%2C%20explaining%20this%20data%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20WPR%20for%20Muslims%20stood%20at%2033.9%25%20in%202020-21%20and%2033.5%25%20in%202021-22.%20It%20declined%20to%2032.5%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20the%20LFPR%20sees%20a%202.6%20percentage%20points%20decline%20%5Bas%20compared%20to%201.8%20percentage%20points%20decline%20in%20the%20WPR.%5D%20This%20shows%20Muslims%20are%20not%20looking%20for%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mehrotra%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F11153131%2Fimage-1380.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221016%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F11153131%2Fimage-1380.png%201016w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F11153131%2Fimage-1380-300x190.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-679491%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22642%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16122914%2Fimage-1391.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22948%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16122914%2Fimage-1391.png%20795w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16122914%2Fimage-1391-300x223.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680296%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22706%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Mehrotra%2C%20this%20is%20clear%20evidence%20that%20the%20Muslims%20have%20taken%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20fall%20in%20jobs%20even%20though%20the%20labour%20market%20should%20have%20revived%20after%20COVID-19.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20%5Bthe%20data%5D%20for%20the%20first%20full%20post-COVID-19%20year%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20explained%20that%20%E2%80%9CMuslims%20have%20a%20higher%20share%20in%20the%20urban%20population%20than%20their%20share%20in%20the%20rural%20population.%20%5BThis%20is%5D%20because%20most%20Muslims%20live%20in%20urban%20areas.%20So%2C%20when%20the%20labour%20market%20revived%20in%20the%20first%20post-COVID%20year%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20has%20been%20a%20sharp%202%20percentage%20point%20decline%20in%20the%20WPR%20of%20Muslims.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%5BNote%20that%5D%20WPR%20tracks%20the%20LFPR%E2%80%A6As%20the%20labour%20market%20revived%2C%20this%20is%20clear%20evidence%20that%20the%20Muslims%20have%20taken%20the%20brunt%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697449069000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16134843%2Fimage-1392.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Funpaid-labour-on-the-rise-muslims-not-looking-for-work-what-the-plfs-data-reveals%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20a%20positive%20note%2C%20the%20data%20shows%20that%20India's%20unemployment%20rate%20has%20reached%20a%20six-year%20low%2C%20standing%20at%203.2%25.%20However%2C%20it's%20essential%20to%20examine%20the%20finer%20details%20to%20gain%20a%20more%20comprehensive%20understanding%20of%20the%20situation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Funpaid-labour-on-the-rise-muslims-not-looking-for-work-what-the-plfs-data-reveals%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22RJD%E2%80%99s%20New%20Spokespersons%3A%20Party%20Ropes%20in%20Young%20Talent%20from%20JNU%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16145757%2Frjd.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(RJD)%20has%20nominated%20three%20PhD%20scholars%20and%20a%20professor%20%E2%80%93%20all%20from%20the%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20(JNU)%20%E2%80%93%20as%20its%20spokespersons%20in%20an%20obvious%20bid%20to%20refurbish%20its%20image%20and%20arm%20itself%20with%20talented%20youngsters%20to%20carry%20forward%20its%20ideological%20battle%20against%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20party%E2%80%99s%20newly%20nominated%20national%20spokespersons%20are%20Jayant%20Jigyasu%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20Media%20Studies%2C%20who%20recently%20submitted%20his%20PhD%20thesis%3B%20Priyanka%20Bharti%2C%20a%20PhD%20scholar%20in%20German%20at%20the%20School%20of%20Languages%3B%20Kanchana%20Yadav%2C%20a%20fellow%20of%20the%20Council%20and%20Scientific%20and%20Industrial%20Research%20(CSIR)%20and%20PhD%20scholar%20at%20the%20School%20of%20Life%20Sciences%3B%20and%20Anwar%20Pasha%2C%20professor%20of%20Urdu%20at%20JNU.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERJD%20secretary%20general%20Abdul%20Bari%20Siddiqui%20issued%20a%20notification%20to%20this%20effect%20at%20the%20instruction%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20national%20president%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20on%20October%2011%2C%20but%20the%20influence%20and%20vision%20of%20Bihar%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%20are%20palpable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20clearly%20reflects%20Tejashwi%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20revamp%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20image.%20The%20RJD%20under%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20stewardship%20has%20carved%20out%20an%20image%20of%20the%20most%20credible%20and%20non-compromising%20regional%20outfit%20fighting%20for%20social%20justice%20and%20secularism.%20But%20it%20is%20also%20known%20as%20the%20party%20of%20the%20rural%20poor%20and%20inarticulate%20sections%20of%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETejashwi%20has%20worked%20in%20a%20sustained%20manner%20to%20mobilise%20students%20and%20scholars%20at%20top%20educational%20institutions%2C%20particularly%20JNU%20and%20Delhi%20University.%20The%20appointment%20of%20Jayant%20Jigyasu%2C%20Priyanka%20Bharti%2C%20Kanchana%20Yadav%20and%20Anwar%20Pasha%20is%20the%20culmination%20of%20a%20six-year%20exercise%20to%20build%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20cadres%2C%20train%20them%20and%20then%20appoint%20them%20as%20important%20office%20bearers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYoung%20talents%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20RJD%20leader%20who%20played%20a%20major%20role%20in%20opening%20the%20student%20wings%20of%20the%20party%20on%20JNU%E2%80%99s%20campus%20is%20Nawal%20Kishore%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20Rajdhani%20College%20at%20Delhi%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20made%20the%20JNU%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20RJD%20students%E2%80%99%20wing%E2%80%99s%20activities%20in%202016-17%2C%20when%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20targeted%20it%20in%20a%20big%20way%20and%20the%20ruling%20establishment%20supported%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sang%20(RSS)%E2%80%99s%20students%E2%80%99%20wing%20Akhil%20Bharatiya%20Vidyarthi%20Parishad%20(ABVP)%20in%20unleashing%20violence%20on%20the%20cadres%20of%20Left%20and%20centrist%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJayant%20Jigyasu%2C%20the%20son%20of%20a%20farmer-school%20teacher%20from%20the%20backward%20Khagaria%20district%20in%20north%20Bihar%2C%20was%20an%20RJD%20cadre%20when%20doing%20his%20under%20graduation%20at%20a%20college%20under%20the%20Bhagalpur%20University%20in%20Bihar.%20He%20carried%20forward%20his%20activism%20when%20he%20joined%20JNU%20as%20an%20MPhil%20student%20in%202017-18.%20He%20unsuccessfully%20contested%20the%20JNU%20Students%E2%80%99%20Union%20presidential%20elections%20in%202018.%20But%20it%20helped%20him%20build%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20cadres%20on%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJayant%E2%80%99s%20father%20participated%20in%20the%20Jayaprakash%20Narayan-led%20movement%20in%20the%201970s.%20His%20parents%20adhered%20to%20%3Cem%3EKabir%20panth%3C%2Fem%3E%20(tenets%20of%20saint%20Kabir)%20that%20inculcated%20in%20him%20liberal%20and%20inclusive%20values.%20He%20was%20on%20the%20RJD%E2%80%99s%20state%20executive%20committee%20prior%20to%20becoming%20the%20spokesperson.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPriyanka%20Bharti%20is%20a%20firebrand%20RJD%20activist%20in%20JNU.%20She%20hails%20from%20a%20humble%20background%20from%20Fatuha%2C%20the%20eastern%20outskirts%20of%20Patna%20district.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20father%20was%20a%20farmer.%20He%20had%20no%20money%20to%20support%20my%20education%20when%20I%20joined%20the%20School%20of%20Languages%20at%20the%20undergraduate%20level%20in%202016.%20I%20tutored%20students%20to%20pay%20for%20my%20education%2C%20something%20that%20I%20still%20do%2C%E2%80%9D%20Priyanka%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20carried%20on%20with%20her%20activism%2C%20leading%20the%20students%20against%20fee%20hikes%20and%20even%20sustaining%20a%20police%20assault.%20The%20RJD%20fielded%20her%20to%20contest%20the%20JNUSU%20presidential%20election%20in%202019.%20She%20didn%E2%80%99t%20win%20but%20made%20a%20mark%20as%20an%20orator.%20Tejashwi%20lashed%20out%20at%20the%20police%20in%20strong%20words%20when%20Priyanka%20suffered%20the%20blow%20of%20the%20police%E2%80%99s%20baton%2C%20adding%20to%20her%20confidence%20in%20the%20party%20and%20Tejashwhi%E2%80%99s%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKanchana%20Yadav%20is%20probably%20the%20most%20studious%20of%20the%20three%20students%20drafted%20as%20spokespersons.%20She%20cracked%20the%20CSIR%20fellowship%20when%20she%20was%20doing%20her%20MSc%20in%20Zoology%20at%20JNU.%20Now%2C%20she%20is%20a%20senior%20fellow%20doing%20research%20on%20cancer.%20She%20is%20from%20the%20Johnpur%20district%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHer%20grandfather%20was%20a%20government%20servant%20and%20her%20father%20worked%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20in%20Mumbai.%20In%20a%20way%2C%20she%20belongs%20to%20a%20relatively%20well-to-do%20family.%20As%20a%20senior%20fellow%20of%20CSIR%2C%20she%20gets%20Rs%2042%2C000%20per%20month%20to%20conduct%20research.%20%E2%80%9CI%20strongly%20believe%20in%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20politics%20of%20social%20justice%20and%20secularism.%20I%20have%20faith%20in%20Tejashwi%E2%80%99s%20leadership%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EProf%20Anwar%20Pasha%20is%20a%20part%20of%20RJD%E2%80%99s%20ideological%20think%20tank.%20He%20has%20worked%20among%20the%20Pasmanda%20(backward)%20Muslims%20and%20has%20produced%20books%20and%20research%20papers%20on%20the%20poor%20sections%20in%20the%20minority%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIdeological%20battle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Nawal%20Kishore%20has%20used%20his%20organisational%20skills%20to%20build%20a%20cadre%20at%20the%20campus%2C%20while%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20Manoj%20Jha%20guided%20them%20in%20ideology%20and%20academics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20all%20have%20unwavering%20faith%20in%20Tejashwi%E2%80%99s%20leadership.%20Be%20it%20the%20issue%20of%20caste%20census%2C%20caste%20survey%20in%20Bihar%2C%20quota%20for%20OBC%20women%20in%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20in%20parliament%20or%20communalism%20and%20hate%20campaign%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindutva%20%3C%2Fem%3Eforces%20%E2%80%93%20these%20young%20RJD%20activists%20dominate%20the%20discourse%20on%20social%20media.%20They%20are%20adept%20at%20advocating%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20line%20and%20countering%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20attacks%20on%20the%20Indian%20National%20Development%20Inclusive%20Alliance%20(INDIA).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20RJD%E2%80%99s%20new%20list%20of%20national%20spokespersons%2C%20issued%20after%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20Bihar%20caste%20survey%2C%20shows%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20social%20justice.%20The%20party%20has%20consistently%20fought%20for%20OBC%20reservation%20and%20an%20OBC%20quota%20in%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20Bill.%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20has%20also%20spoken%20about%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ejiski%20jitni%20sankhya%20bhaari%2C%20uski%20utni%20hissedari%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20share%20in%20power%20in%20proportion%20to%20the%20numerical%20strength).%20Jayant%2C%20Priyanka%20and%20Kanchana%20are%20all%20from%20OBC%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENalin%20Verma%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%2C%20author%2C%20media%20educator%2C%20and%20independent%20researcher%20in%20folklore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697448676000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16145757%2Frjd.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Frjd-new-spokespersons-young-talent-jnu%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20influence%20and%20vision%20of%20Bihar%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%20are%20palpable%20in%20the%20appointments%20of%20Jayant%20Jigyasu%2C%20Kanchana%20Yadav%2C%20Priyanka%20Bharti%20and%20Anwar%20Pasha.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A97%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Frjd-new-spokespersons-young-talent-jnu%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mahua%20Moitra%20Sends%20Legal%20Notice%20to%20BJP's%20Nishikant%20Dubey%2C%20Advocate%20for%20'False%2C%20Defamatory%20Allegations'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F17150248%2FUntitled-design-15-e1679045890144.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3ETrinamool%20Congress%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20Mahua%20Moitra%20has%20sent%20legal%20notices%20to%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20MP%20Nishikant%20Dubey%20and%20advocate%20Jai%20Anant%20Dehadrai%20for%20making%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%20and%20defamatory%20allegations%E2%80%9D%20against%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDubey%20had%20alleged%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20speaker%20on%20Sunday%20that%20Moitra%20was%20given%20%E2%80%9Ccash%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cgifts%E2%80%9D%20as%20bribes%20to%20ask%20questions%20about%20the%20Adani%20Group%20in%20parliament.%20He%20claimed%20to%20have%20received%20information%20about%20this%20from%20Dehadrai.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%20not%20responded%20to%20queries%20raised%20by%20Moitra%20and%20other%20opposition%20parties%20about%20allegations%20against%20the%20Adani%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20notice%20from%20Moitra%20was%20also%20issued%20to%2018%20media%20and%20social%20media%20platforms%20which%20reported%20the%20news%2C%20including%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20notice%20points%20out%20that%20Moitra%20had%20recently%20raised%20questions%20about%20the%20veracity%20of%20Dubey%E2%80%99s%20claimed%20educational%20qualifications%20and%20said%20that%20he%20had%20lied%20on%20his%20election%20affidavit.%20This%2C%20the%20notice%20says%2C%20had%20%E2%80%9Crattled%E2%80%9D%20Dubey%20and%20so%20he%20was%20now%20making%20these%20false%20allegations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Dehadrai%2C%20the%20notice%20says%20that%20Moitra%20and%20the%20advocate%20used%20to%20be%20close%20friends%2C%20but%20had%20a%20falling%20out.%20After%20that%2C%20Dehadrai%20allegedly%20%E2%80%9Crepeatedly%20threatened%20our%20Client%20%5BMoitra%5D%20with%20several%20vile%2C%20malicious%20and%20vulgar%20messages%E2%80%9D%20and%20trespassed%20on%20her%20official%20residence%20and%20stole%20personal%20possessions%2C%20including%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20dog.%20The%20legal%20notice%20says%20the%20dog%20was%20later%20returned.%20After%20repeated%20violations%2C%20Moitra%20had%20filed%20police%20complaints%20against%20Dehadrai.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDehadrai%20tried%20to%20get%20journalists%20to%20publish%20false%20stories%20about%20Moitra%2C%20the%20notice%20says%2C%20but%20could%20not%20convince%20anyone%20because%20of%20the%20lack%20of%20evidence%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20soon%20after%20convincing%20our%20Client%20%5BMoitra%5D%20to%20withdraw%20the%20%5Bpolice%5D%20Complaints%20dated%2025%20March%202023%20and%2023%20September%202023%2C%20Noticee%20No.%202%20%5BDehadrai%5D%20immediately%20zapped%20back%20to%20old%20ways%20and%20continued%20his%20misguided%20and%20malicious%20pursuit%20of%20vendetta%20against%20our%20Client.%20Noticee%20No.%202%20reached%20out%20to%20several%20prominent%20journalists%20and%20attempted%20to%20convince%20them%20to%20run%20stories%20based%20on%20wild%2C%20vindictive%2C%20fictitious%20and%20entirely%20imaginary%20allegations%20about%20our%20Client.%20It%20appears%20that%20no%20credible%20journalist%20responded%20to%20Noticee%20No.%202%E2%80%99s%20desperate%20attempts%20to%20malign%20our%20Client%E2%80%99s%20reputation%20basis%20unsupported%20and%20unsubstantiated%20allegations%20without%20even%20a%20shred%20of%20evidence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20journalists%20could%20not%20be%20convinced%2C%20Dehadrai%20then%20approached%20the%20BJP%20and%20Dubey%2C%20the%20notice%20states.%20Dubey%20then%20went%20on%20to%20repeat%20these%20allegations%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdid%20not%20even%20bother%20to%20conduct%20any%20due%20diligence%20of%20any%20kind%20to%20establish%20the%20veracity%20of%20the%20allegations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNot%20only%20did%20Noticee%20No.%201%20%5BDubey%5D%20relay%2C%20endorse%20and%20exaggerate%20the%20false%2C%20baseless%20and%20per%20se%20defamatory%20allegations%20against%20our%20Client%20%5BMoitra%5D%2C%20but%20also%20proceeded%20to%20leak%20the%20same%20to%20members%20of%20the%20media.%20Noticee%20No.%201%20and%202%20%5BDehadrai%5D%20are%20both%20directly%20responsible%20for%20defaming%20and%20maligning%20the%20reputation%20and%20goodwill%20of%20our%20Client%20for%20their%20own%20respective%20personal%20and%20political%20vendettas%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20legal%20notice%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20notice%20also%20makes%20clear%20that%20Moitra%20rejects%20the%20allegations%20made%20as%20completely%20baseless%3A%20%E2%80%9COur%20Client%20has%20never%20accepted%20any%20remuneration%20or%20cash%20or%20gift%20or%20benefit%20of%20any%20kind%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20discharge%20of%20her%20duties%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Parliament%2C%20including%20but%20not%20limited%20to%2C%20the%20questions%20raised%20by%20her%20in%20Parliament%20and%20any%20suggestion%20to%20the%20contrary%20is%20vehemently%20denied%20by%20our%20Client.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20notice%20also%20says%20that%20Dubey%20and%20Dehadrai%20have%20leaked%20private%20photos%20of%20Moitra%20after%20cropping%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20notice%20calls%20upon%20Dubey%20to%20withdraw%20his%20letter%20to%20the%20speaker%20and%20all%20allegations%2C%20and%20issue%20a%20public%20apology%20to%20Moitra.%20Dehadrai%20has%20also%20been%20asked%20to%20withdraw%20the%20allegations%20in%20all%20communications%20and%20issue%20a%20public%20apology.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697448042000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F17150248%2FUntitled-design-15-e1679045890144.jpg