0%E2%80%9Cinvolved%20in%20the%20activity%20of%20submission%20to%20UN%20Global%20Impact%20to%20delist%20Adani%20Ports%2C%20which%20is%20not%20as%20per%20the%20objects%20of%20the%20assessee%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20letter%20to%20Environics%20Trust%2C%20the%20department%20said%20that%20the%20trust%20collaborated%20with%20the%20Mineral%20Inheritors%20Right%20Association%20for%20protesting%20against%20Jindal%20Steel%20Works%20and%20Adani%20Coal%20Projects%20in%20Odisha%20and%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20as%20per%20the%20objects%20of%20the%20Trust%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Famidst-cancellations-of-thousands-of-ngos-licences-ram-mandir-applies-for-fcra-licence%5C%22%3EAmidst%20Cancellations%20Of%20Thousands%20Of%20NGOs%E2%80%99%20Licences%2C%20Ram%20Mandir%20Trust%20Applies%20For%20FCRA%20Licence%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApart%20from%20reasons%20mentioned%20above%2C%20the%20income%20tax%20department%E2%80%99s%20letter%20to%20Oxfam%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newslaundry.com%2F2023%2F10%2F14%2Fi-t-dept-revokes-tax-exemption-status-of-4-ngos-letters-to-two-mention-protests-against-adani%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20NGO%20was%20%E2%80%9Cinvolved%20in%20questioning%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20government%20and%20discussing%20political%20issues%20in%20the%20meeting%2C%20which%20do%20not%20align%20with%20the%20objects%20of%20the%20assessee%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20alleged%20that%20the%20organisation%20was%20%E2%80%9Cworking%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20a%20particular%20community%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3ENewsLaundry%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20letter%20to%20Environics%20Trust%2C%20the%20department%20said%20the%20organisation%20was%20%E2%80%9Cinvolved%20in%20Dhinkia%20protests%20against%20JSW%20Plants%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EResidents%20of%20Dhinkia%20village%20in%20Odisha%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fodisha-jindal-plant-20-houses-demolished-dhinkia%5C%22%3Eprotesting%20against%20the%20transfer%20of%20over%201%2C000%20hectares%20of%20land%20to%20Jindal%20Steel%20Works%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20setting%20up%20a%2013.2%20million%20tonnes%20steel%20plant%20unit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20had%20alleged%20that%20the%20project%20and%20the%20corporate%20takeover%20of%20the%20land%20will%20lead%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fodisha-jindal-plant-20-houses-demolished-dhinkia%5C%22%3Edevastation%20of%20livelihoods%20of%20over%2040%2C000%20villagers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20will%20impact%20three%20villages%20of%20Dhinkia%2C%20Nuagaon%20and%20Gadakujang%20in%20the%20district.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Raising%20questions%20against%20industries%20has%20become%20illegal%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOfficials%20at%20CARE%20India%20and%20LIFE%20chose%20not%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20revocation%20of%20their%20tax%20status.%20An%20official%20at%20the%20former%20told%20%3Cem%3ENewslaundry%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20they%20did%20not%20want%20to%20divulge%20any%20specifics%20from%20the%20I-T%20department%E2%80%99s%20letter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newslaundry.com%2F2023%2F10%2F14%2Fi-t-dept-revokes-tax-exemption-status-of-4-ngos-letters-to-two-mention-protests-against-adani%5C%22%3Efearing%20backlash%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20officials%20at%20LIFE%20said%20that%20they%20were%20%E2%80%9Ccurrently%20studying%20the%20options%20and%20have%20no%20specific%20comments%20to%20make%E2%80%9D%2C%20those%20at%20Environics%20said%20they%20were%20likely%20to%20challenge%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Order%20in%20the%20court%20coming%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERamamurthi%20Sreedhar%2C%20earth%20scientist%20and%20member%20of%20the%20core%20working%20team%20at%20the%20trust%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20the%20order%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20our%20behaviour%20as%20an%20organisation.%20It%20is%20just%20that%20raising%20questions%20against%20the%20industries%20in%20India%20has%20become%20illegal%20now.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20revocation%20of%20tax%20status%20has%20come%20amid%20an%20ongoing%20attack%20on%20NGOs%20across%20the%20country%20which%2C%20according%20to%20civil%20society%20members%20and%20political%20analysts%2C%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20suppress%20organisations%20that%20are%20critical%20of%20the%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20September%202022%2C%20the%20I-T%20department%20had%20surveyed%20the%20offices%20of%20Oxfam%20India%2C%20Care%20India%2C%20Life%2C%20Environics%20Trust%2C%20CPR%20and%20Independent%20and%20Public%20Spirited%20Media%20Foundation%20(IPSMF)%2C%20%3Cem%3ENewsLaundry%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20top%20official%20at%20CARE%20India%20told%20%3Cem%3ENewsLaundry%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20raid%20was%20a%20part%20of%20a%20plot%20by%20the%20government.%20As%20part%20of%20a%20tax%20survey%20in%202022%2C%20they%20seized%20our%20computers%20and%20laptops%2C%20kept%20our%20staff%20locked%20in%20the%20Delhi%20office%20for%2072%20hours.%20Our%20staff%20was%20not%20allowed%20to%20go%20out.%20And%20not%20just%20Delhi%2C%20but%20our%20offices%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20Surat%20were%20also%20raided.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20FCRA%20licences%20(under%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20Regulations%20Act)%20of%20Oxfam%2C%20LIFE%20and%20Environics%20Trust%20have%20already%20been%20cancelled.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697446251000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16134849%2F36877237784_9786faab2d_c.