ia%20Ethics%20Code)%20Amendment%20Rules%2C%202023.%20These%20amended%20IT%20Rules%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fit-rules-amendment-legal-complications%5C%22%3E%20empower%20a%20fact-checking%20committee%20appointed%20by%20the%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20call%20for%20the%20taking%20down%20of%20any%20information%20it%20deems%20fake%20or%20false%20or%20misleading.%20This%20has%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Feditors-guild-it-amendment-rules-fact-checking%5C%22%3Eled%20to%20serious%20questions%20of%20censorship%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Standard%E2%80%99s%20report%20highlights%20that%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20has%20sent%20a%20memorandum%20to%20these%20abovementioned%20digital%20platforms%20as%20part%20of%20its%20attempt%20to%20quell%20misinformation%20ahead%20of%20assembly%20elections%20to%20five%20states%20this%20year%20and%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20memorandums%20have%20it%20that%20the%20significant%20social%20media%20intermediaries%20%E2%80%93%20SSMIs%20%E2%80%93%20should%20send%20the%20government%20%E2%80%98action%20taken%20reports%E2%80%99%20within%2010%20days%20on%20%E2%80%9Cdispelling%20fake%20news%20and%20unlawful%20content.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20YouTube%2C%20the%20memorandum%20highlights%20that%20the%20website%20should%20add%20a%20ticker%20with%20news%20channels%20whose%20%E2%80%9Cnews%20is%20not%20verified.%E2%80%9D%20It%20should%20also%20introduce%20appropriate%20policy%20to%20take%20legal%20action%20against%20channels%20which%20show%20allegedly%20fake%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20the%20largest%20YouTube%20user%20population%2C%20with%20467%20million%20active%20users.%20The%20number%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fforecasts%2F1146150%2Fyoutube-users-in-india%5C%22%3Eforecast%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20recommendations%20were%20devi